<Author>co_rich_car
<Content>H10 Marina Barcelona Hotel is a great value! My husband and I recently stayed in this hotel for four days prior to a twelve day cruise leaving from Barcelona. It was part of a package deal booked through Air France and we were very pleased. For a moderate price hotel, this was an excellent value. Even though it's location is not in the heart of the city, it is an easy walk to bus and Metro stops or the staff can order a taxi for you. Our room was spacious, comfortable and quiet. The mattress was a little firmer than you customarily find in the States, but it was not an issue. The service was excellent throughtout the entire stay beginning with a glass of champagne when we arrived to obtaining taxi service to the pier at departure time. The staff at the front desk all speak enough English to communicate easily. They were very helpful in assisting with our sightseeing efforts. Prior to leaving on our trip, I had read reviews about this hotel and the amazing breakfast that is part of the stay. I could not fully appreciate it until I had the experience the first day. What an incredible display of the most delicious food! I have never seen anything to compare in this country. The variety is unbelievable such as champagne, Spanish ham, multiple types of eggs, nuts, local cheeses, breads, yogurt, pastries, juices, and fresh and dried fruits with exotic varieties. You can make healthy choices, including specific foods for diabetics, or be totally decadent and at the same time experience the culture. 
