<Author>tsaunders
<Content>Nice hotel, friendly staff, great food My husband and I stayed at the Marina for 3 nights in December 2005. We managed to get a very special rate - 拢180 for 3 nights on a BB basis, so shop around before you book! The hotel is only 3-5 minutes walk from Bogatell metro, which then takes you into the heart of Barcelona in around 10 mins. The fare is very reasonable (around 80p for a single journey) and the service frequent until late at night.The hotel greets guests with a glass of cava when they check in (although we missed out on this because they were busy), and we even got a chocolate on our pillow on the first night be stayed with them. The room was clean, well decorated, and well stocked with everything from combs, toothbrushes to the usual shower gel etc. The minibar was also well stocked at the usual prices.The hotel bar on the ground floor was manned with friendly bar staff, but little touches such as bowls of nuts, often seen at other hotels of this standard, were missing. The tapas bar was never open in the 3 days we were at the hotel, despite adverts to the contrary.The restaurant evening meals were good quality, reasonably priced, and there was free cava and 'nibbles' buffet to start. The buffet breakfast was fantastic, really good range of everything from fruits, cakes, cheese, meats and bread - even cava again!We never got to try the spa facilities, as there was so much to see in the town. We walked 5 minutes down to Port Olimpic and joined the Bus Turistic on 2 days - hop on hop off for 2 days 21 Euros each - 2 separate routes covering all the well- and lesser-known sights in the town. We highly recommend this! Port Olimpic also has loads of bars and restaurants, mainly featuring seafood, but we found some veggie stuff too!All in all, a fantastic hotel in a handy location. 
