<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Not too close, not too far The H10 Marina Barcelona hotel is quite new with modern furnishings, decor and artwork. We had champagne on arrival and our luggage was brought to our room. The room, also modern in style was long and narrow, with a great bathroom and showed a few signs of wear and tear. Breakfast in the morning is buffet style, with a lot of choice. The restaurant meal was nice, but it lacked atmosphere. Overall the hotel was good, but the walls are paper thin and we could hear everything in the rooms eitherside of us, not nice.The location of the hotel is great. Its near the Parc de la Ciutadella, the largest park in Barcelona which has the zoo, with 400 species of animal and also the site of the Catalan Parliament. Great for romantic walks on route to any excursion. We found ourselves to be walking distance to the beach, La Rambla, Barri Gotic and Placa de Catalunya, the centre point of the city to get the airport bus, the metro (underground), tourist information and the central pick up point for the Barcelona Bus Turistic's three routes around the city (the green route runs in the summer only). The bus Turistic is the best way to see the city and isn't expensive, you can hop on and off as often as you like. The red route was our favourite, anything Gaudi, and in particular Park Guell and La Pedrera. On the blue route the favourite was Barri Gotic (The Gothic Quarter), the city's 2000 year old historical origins, built on the old Roman town. Its absolutely beautiful and has the Musea d'Historia, the Cathedral, the Picasso museaum and also great shops, boutiques etc. Its a fantastic city, which has something to offer everyone. 
