<Content>Good hotel on the whole. Stayed here mid-March 2004 and was on the whole pretty pleased. For the price the rooms are spacious, well cleaned and freshly designed. Beds are huge, if a little hard for some tastes. Food was excellent, as everyone has already said a massive variety of breakfasts is available. We ate one evening in the restaurant too, and this was equally impressive.Staff were on the whole very helpful although i was disapointed that the Wellness Centre (spa/pool etc) facilities were not free to all guests (12.50 euros each) and told them as such. Nowhere in their literature does it state that you pay extra for this. Also these facilities are open at pretty useless times if a weekend visitor (1-7pm)The free internet access in the business suite was very useful and the bar/reception area was very pleasant - note the bar is only open until 12 though. As for its location, well we found it perfect. Metro is a short walk away, quick and reliable. Had no reason to use a cab during our stay. 10 minute walk to the beach / marina (pretty lively at night!) and 15 minutes to the gothic quarter.All in all would recommend this hotel as long as you dont insist on being in the thick of the action or are expecting spa facilities to be included. Loved Barcelona by the way! 
