<Content>A room with a view. We (my wife and I) were a bit apprehensive before we had even arrived as we had booked the Easyjet flight and the hotel reservation over the internet, this is the first time we had done anything like this but must say that it was so easy. We stayed at the H10 Marina hotel from November 26-29 during which we had a wonderful time. The funny thing was though, we were supposed to be staying at the H10 Itica in the city and not the Marina, there were air conditioning problems at the Hotel Itica so when we arrived we were transferred directly to the H10 Marina hotel. The hotel Maria is modern, clean and very comfortable, We were told that the hotel had been completed earlier in the year. We were fortunate to be staying on the top floor, which gave us views of the sea the city and the countryside. The room was perfect, very spacious, comfortable and clean. The bathroom was nicely finished in marble and had everything you could need for a short stay. The hotel is in my opinion, located in a great area. It is just a few minutes walking distance to two metro stations and the marina area where there are plenty of restaurants and clubs. The only down side was the fact that the area around the hotel is being developed, with that in mind I will say that there was no noise form the neighbouring building sites. The hotel is only a stones throw away from what was once the Olympic Village , it is also within walking distance of the Blue Tourist bus route which was a god send for my wife and I, not having been to Barcelona before we did both the Blue and the Red routes the first day we arrived, then on the second using our two day bus pass we travelled back to the sights we wanted to take a closer look at, and were not disappointed. The hotel breakfast was really good and had a wide selection of items to choose from, fruit juice, yoghurt, fresh fruit, cereals, eggs bacon through to croissants all served with tea or coffee. Unfortunately there were no tea or coffee making facilities in the room which we could have done with, you know what it s like when you just want to sit down with a nice cup of tea and your feet up. There is a small wine bar from which you can participate in tastings, there is also a bar in the main lobby where you can have a drink before going out on the town. On the roof there is also a small but nice pool, the hotel also boasts a health centre which, costs approximately $10 Euros a day to use. All of the staff were friendly and helpful, from the moment we arrived right up to when we left, they all spoke very good English (apart from the porter, he struggled a bit) A most enjoyable stay in an ideal location, it could not have suited us better, just a little way from the main attractions of the city. I will definitely be returning to Barcelona as soon as possible. 
